rows.head: Definitions
rows.content: Conda is an application for data science package management and environment management. It is primarily used for managing Python packages, though it also supports R, Ruby, Lua, Scala, Java, JavaScript, C, C++, and Fortran packages
rows.code:
# Display Conda version with conda --version
# Display Conda system info with conda info
# Get help on Conda with conda --help
# Get help on Conda command usage with conda {command} --help
conda --version
conda info
docker --
docker build --
help
help
